    "introduction": "Few would have guessed that \"Weird Al\" Yankovic - who as a shy, accordion-playing teenager got his start sending in homemade tapes to the Dr. Demento Radio Show - would go on to become a pop culture icon and the biggest-selling comedy recording artist of all time, with classic song and music video parodies such as \"Eat It,\" \"Like a Surgeon,\" \"Smells Like Nirvana,\" \"Amish Paradise,\" \"White & Nerdy\" and \"Word Crimes.\" Now in his fourth decade as America's foremost song parodist, he has been honored with four Grammy® Awards and fifteen nominations, including a 2015 win for his 14th studio album Mandatory Fun.",
